text.tspan: + folding instructions
dowload the template and print (with page scaling turned off) onto ISO a4 paper.
lay onto a flat hard surface and turn the template over.
> step one (1)
fold along the lines labeled 1, then unfold flat
> step two (2)
fold along the line labeled 2, then unfold flat
> step three (3)
fold along the lines labeled 3 to provide
a shape like the first image. do the same
to the remaining lines labeled 3 so that
the template can lie flat.
> step four (4)
fold along the lines labeled 4 to create a 'dog-ear' corner.
> step five (5)
fold along the line labeled 5 to create the securing flap.
should you need to write on the case do it now.
insert the disk data side inward.
Template drawn by
Xan Manning
github.com/xanmanning/ISO-A4-CD-Case
